potato 22-Sep-18 07:39 AM
Is there a way to use FindUnitsInRadius to restrict the number of a certain unit to spawn, kinda like how the DataDriven Spawnunit unitlimit works but inside lua? Because I use lua to spawn my units.
Quark 22-Sep-18 07:45 AM
why do you need to limit findunitsinradius? it gives you an integer-indexed table anyway
potato 22-Sep-18 07:51 AM
Sorry as with alot of people, i'm quite new to the whole lua side of things so could you explain what you mean by that?
Quark 22-Sep-18 07:57 AM
FindUnitsInRadius returns a lua table that uses numbers as its indexing
so you do like
local units = FindUnitsInRadius(...)
and then you can do
units[1] to get the first unit that was found
units[2] gets the second, etc
so you can just loop through the table until you've hit the maximum amount of units you want
say you want only the first 3 units, it'll be something like
local units = FindUnitsInRadius(...) for i = 1, 3 do units[i] -- do something with units[i] here end
